    <section id="healthy-plate">
      <h2>Building a Healthy Plate</h2>

      <article>
        <h3>Nutrition for Basketball Players</h3>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1490645935967-10de6ba17061?w=300&h=200&fit=crop"
            alt="Healthy meal with fruits, vegetables, and protein"
            width="300"
            height="200"
          >
          <figcaption>
            Athletes need balanced meals to stay energized and perform at their best.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <p>
          Basketball players need healthy meals that include protein, fruits,
          vegetables, and whole grains. Good nutrition helps improve energy,
          recovery, and performance on the court.
        </p>

        <p>
          Learn more here:
          <a href="https://www.myplate.gov/" target="_blank">
            MyPlate Nutrition Guide
          </a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h3>Smart Snacks Before Practice</h3>

        <figure>
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1498837167922-ddd27525d352?w=300&h=200&fit=crop"
            alt="Healthy snacks including fruit and nuts"
            width="300"
            height="200"
          >
          <figcaption>
            Healthy snacks help athletes stay fueled throughout the day.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <p>
          Good pre-practice snacks include bananas, yogurt, nuts, and whole-grain foods.
          These foods provide lasting energy without making you feel sluggish.
        </p>

        <p>
          Read more here:
          <a href="https://www.nutrition.gov/" target="_blank">
            Nutrition.gov
          </a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="nutrition-tips">
      <h2>Nutrition Tips for Students</h2>

      <article>
        <h3>Drink More Water</h3>

        <p>
          Water keeps your body hydrated and helps athletes perform better.
          Carrying a water bottle during school and sports is a good habit.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h3>Choose Healthy Foods</h3>

        <p>
          Try to eat colorful fruits and vegetables every day. Different colors
          provide different nutrients that help your body stay healthy.
        </p>

        <p>
          Learn more:
          <a href="https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/healthy-diet" target="_blank">
            WHO Healthy Diet Guide
          </a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

